Description:
Presumed BRN gunmen killed Pol Sen Cpl Nathawut Surat, a police officer on secondment to Sai Buri Police Station, in an attack at Sai Buri Police Station, Tabing Subdistrict, Sai Buri District, Pattani on 22 May 2026, using four war-grade firearms. Nathawut was shot and seriously wounded and subsequently died at Sai Buri Crown Prince Hospital. Forensic analysis by Forensic Science Center 10 subsequently linked the 66 shell casings recovered at the scene to four weapons:

- one AK-47 (7.62mm Russian; 17 casings, linked to 9 prior incidents spanning 2023–2026);
- one AK-102 (.223/5.56mm; 17 casings, linked to 46 prior incidents dating to January 2012);
- one HK-33 (.223/5.56mm; 13 casings, linked to 3 prior incidents);
- one M16 (.223/5.56mm; 19 casings, linked to 1 prior incident).

The linked incidents span over 14 years and include the killing of volunteer fighters, soldiers, police officers, and civilians across Sai Buri, Kapho, Mai Kaen, Mayo, and Pana-re Districts in Pattani.
